<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="b6a990605aa6b8e44ba964b8bf194884" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> LOTR Q&A Rulings from 03/18/04<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.50)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617'>Enrique "Max of Tat" Huerta</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 8, 2004</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Not for review.<br />
Originally posted 03/18/04.<br />
===========================<br />
<br />
<br />
Hello All!!<br />
<br />
  Back from Vegas! I had a blast last weekend and I wanted to say it was great to see so many of you. As always I&#39;m looking for ways to improve the Con experience for the players. If you have any suggestions, please pass them along to me and I&#39;ll see what I can do. Thank you. Unfortunately, I don&#39;t think I&#39;ll be able to make it to another Con until GenCon in July.<br />
<br />
  This update is a little light, but I think we cover some good questions here. I expect a lot more next time because Siege of Gondor just released. So keep sending in those questions! (=<br />
<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Card Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>Do you know of any article anywhere, or some explanation, which clarifies the game text on the cards that say &quot;every minion gains this ability: assign this minion to the bearer of [this card]&quot;?  I hope that isn&#39;t confusing.  I think this came out with RotK, and I have never understood it. [Helen]</b><br />
<br />
Just imagine that Reckless Pride is on Gimli and that each minion has the game text &quot;Assignment: Assign this minion to Gimli.&quot;<br />
<br />
Now during assignment actions YOU (not the Free People&#39;s Player) gets to decide who fights Gimli. It&#39;s important to remember two things:<br />
1. Assignment Actions happen before the FPP assigns defenders. So you would have to play this action before you see what the FPP is going to do.<br />
2. Assignment Actions must all was involve unassigned characters and must resolve in one-to-one assignements. So only 1 of your minions may be assigned to Gimli, you can&#39;t assign them all to him.<br />
<br />
Now just apply those same rules to each version of the card and replace &quot;Gimli&quot; with the title of the character bearing it.<br />
<br />
<b>I have a question involving the Morgul Squealer from SOG. <br />
<br />
Are you aloud to discard him from your hand to play 2 (ringwraith) minions from your drawdeck at -1 each (or to play one from your discard pile), or do you have to play him first then use his ability to discard him? [Melkor]</b><br />
<br />
The default definition of &quot;discard&quot; is &quot;discard from play&quot;. As such, the Morgul Squealer must be in play to use his Shadow action.<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Game/Tournament Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>Well I am wondering about this new card Promise Keeping. It says response: each time a companion takes a wound in a skirmish that involved a [gollum] minion, exert a companion. I was asking about you&#39;re a liar and a thief (YaLaaT)with this and it was confirmed by some joe on the message boards that YaLaaT still happens during the skirmish and triggers the card. This person then brought up the fact that if you kill a comp during a skirmish with say Gollum or Shelob then any threat wounds placed are wounds that occur during that skirmish so they also trigger Promise Keeping. Is this true? And if so is that what they intended? It seems a little too good... It not only doubles the threat wounds but allows you to &#39;choose&#39; where half of them are placed. Also if this is legit, Can you hold onto YaLaaT and then use it as a response somewhere in the middle of the threat wound placement or only at the end of the threat wound placement/ Promise Keeping exertions, or is it too late to play it at the end? I would think you could as a response is optional and the placing of threat wounds is mandatory. It just seems too good. Thanks as always for your great work. [Tubbadelic]</b><br />
<br />
Lots of questions, but the answer to most of them is &quot;Yes.&quot;. Let me try to explain.<br />
<br />
Once you start a skirmish phase, you&#39;re in a skirmish (skimishing, assigned to a skirmish, etgully-boonteril a winner/loser is determined and all actions triggered by winning/losing have resolved. These actions include mandatory actions (placing wounds, overwhelming, Worry, etc.) and optional actions (Twilight Witch-king, You&#39;re a Liar and a Thief, stacking on Goblin Swarms, etc.). Each of these actions themselves do not completely resolve until all actions triggers by them resolve.<br />
<br />
So... if a companion loses to Gollum, the mandatory actions include placing a wound or overwhelming the companion. If that results in a companion dying, the actions are to place the companion in the dead pile, which in turn triggers the threat. (NOTE: We are still in a skirmish because all actions to winning/losing have yet to resolve.) As each of these threats are placed, Promise Keeping would trigger and the Shadow player would be able to assign exertions. That was all from the mandatory action of Gollum winning and the companion losing. Next are optional actions, like You&#39;re a Liar and a Thief. Again, we&#39;re still in the skirmish so you could still trigger Promise Keeping to add an exertion.<br />
<br />
When everything resolves, the skirmish is end and the next one (or the regroup phase) begins.<br />
<br />
<b>Enrique, <br />
I keep hearing that you can use faramir, wizard&#39;s pupil to absorb threat wounds but I fail to understand how it works. Can you simply exert gandalf and say all threat wounds go to faramir therefore nullifying threats while he is on the table? Otherwise how does it work? Also, has this been officially ruled on? I just ask because I am going to be attending a TOC soon and want to be able to show the TD where that is stated if the issue comes up in a game. Thanks in advance for your help. [The Lucky] </b><br />
<br />
Yes. As mentioned above, a skirmish does not end until all actions triggered by winning/losing have resolved. Faramir, Wizard&#39;s Pupil&#39;s skirmish action prevents all wound to him until the end of the skirmish. So throughout that entire process above if any wounds were to be applied to Faramir (including Threat wounds) they would be prevented. (Note: If the wounds are prevented, that also means Promise Keeping does NOT trigger.) Just remember to exert Gandalf during the skirmish actions part of the phase. Once you determine the winner/loser, it&#39;s too late to use Faramir&#39;s skimish action.<br />
<br />
Here&#39;s an old ruling of mine on this topic: (1/8/04)<br />
<i>Faramir, wizards pupil can exert gandalf to prevent all wounds to faramir. My question is, what happens if someone is about to die, so as a skirmish action the free peoples player exerts gandalf, and the threat wounds are triggered, can faramir &#39;suck them up&#39;? can you assign them to him, but because he&#39;s superman, they bounce off, never to be seen again? thanks! [Machine]</i><br />
<br />
Cards that prevent wounds are different than cards that limit the amount of wounds a character can receive. The best example is Gimli&#39;s Helm, since it has both functions.<br />
<br />
While wearing his helm, Gimli may only take 1 wound per skirmish phase. Regardless of the source, only 1 wound per skirmish phase may be placed on Gimli. Any wounds over that limit must be placed on a different valid target. So if you were applying 3 threat wounds, only 1 could be placed on Gimli while the rest would have to be placed on other valid companions. If Gimli lost a skirmish to a minion that was Damage +2, only 1 wound would be placed on Gimli. The other 2 wounds that he should have taken would not be placed on anyone, since there is only one valid target for placing wounds for losing a skirmish.<br />
<br />
If as a Skirmish Action, you discard the helm all wounds that were to be placed on Gimli in this skirmish phase would be ignored and have no effect. So in the above examples, you could apply all 3 threat wounds to Gimli, but they would have 0 effect on him. Gimli would also take no wounds for losing a Skirmish to a Damage +2 minion.<br />
<br />
Cards like Gimli&#39;s Helm (Skirmish Action) and Faramir, Wizard&#39;s Pupil are great ways of safely dealing with threat wounds.<br />
<br />
<h3>Star Wars:CCG Rulings</h3><br />
<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
